      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHIEF KENNY (1) has been a bit costly as a beaten favourite at his last couple but he continues to race well, boxing on for fourth last time after kicking off his career with back-to-seconds. Draws on the pegs today so this could be his chance. MAJARO GIRL (6) turned in a strong effort at her latest outing, coming from a similar barrier to get home by 1.4m at this circuit and distance. She could go on with it now that the penny has dropped. HILLDALE HILTON (5) gets his lowest draw yet and has been good in his last two outings, winning two back before racing parked and sticking on for a 2.5m second last time. SUMMER KISS (3) lines up for the first time. By Classic Connection and hails from the Rickie Alchin stable. Has shown some ability at the trials so worth keeping safe.",
